this repo will deploy on master push to:
https://arena.meetup.to
https://toronto-arena.herokuapp.com

Are.na Toronto meetup mini-server built with go.

Purpose of this site is to leverage server-side functionality
in place of front-end func with javascript. specifically 
rendering "29" or "Leap Day" in the description. "Leap Day"
has a 1 in 4 chance of being called. (THIS IS NOT TRUE ON THIS
BRANCH LOL ðŸ˜”)

In order to run
$ now dev
then make a request to localhost:3000

Initial setup for heroku
$ govendor init 
$ git init; git add .; git commit -m "init";
$ heroku create to-arena
$ git push heroku master

